#X text 433 61 Fortunately \, we can use a backlash to escape special
characters such as "$". As such \, in order to have a literal "\$0"
we can use a backlash to escape it. And since this prevent it from
being expanded \, it actually even works inside message moxes. Hence
\, the options below enable a literal "\$0" and the receive symbol
gets saved unexpanded in the patch., f 54;
